description: SOPerior Fertilizer Corp. engages in the exploration, evaluation, and development of mineral properties and related projects in the United States and Canada. The company explores for alunite deposits to produce sulphate of potash, sulphuric acid, and alumina. Its principal mineral project is the Blawn Mountain project covering an area of approximately 11,550 acres located in Beaver County, Utah. The company was formerly known as Potash Ridge Corporation and changed its name to SOPerior Fertilizer Corp. in June 2018. SOPerior Fertilizer Corp. was incorporated in 2011 and is headquartered in Toronto, Canada.
ceo: Mr. Andrew  Squires B.Sc., P. Eng, P.Eng.
